  <Body>
    <Heading level="1">
      <TitleText>Short Title</TitleText>
    </Heading>
    <Section lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2003-01-01" lims:id="115007">
      <MarginalNote>Short title</MarginalNote>
      <Label>1</Label>
      <Text>This Act may be cited as the Criminal Code.</Text>
    </Section>
    <Heading level="1">
      <TitleText>Interpretation</TitleText>
    </Heading>
    <Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-18" lims:lastAmendedDate="2023-01-14" lims:id="115012">
      <MarginalNote>Definitions</MarginalNote>
      <Label>2</Label>
      <Text>In this Act, bodily harm means any hurt or injury to a person that interferes with the health or comfort of the person and that is more than merely transient or trifling in nature.</Text>
    </Section>
